stylometry: A transportation proplem looks at moving goods form point A to point B. However, a transshipment problem, a more complex transportation problem, looks at moving good from point A to point B but through point C. Transhippment problems have warehouse where transportation problems do not. Both types of probelms are looking at minimizing the cost of moving the goods. A node is the starting point, ending point and an points in between. Arcs are the paths that the goods follow between the nodes and the flow is the rate at which the goods flow between the nodes. An example of a transhipment problem would be a company wants to ship pants to all of its retailers across the country, in order to de so they have set up warehouse to hold the pants after they are made in their factories.
